WEBVTT

00:04.304 --> 00:05.271 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.305 --> 00:06.272 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.306 --> 00:08.008 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.041 --> 00:12.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY, White House
Budget Director:
We're trying to drive the
economic benefit

00:12.112 --> 00:14.948 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
here to the taxpayers in the
middle.

00:14.981 --> 00:20.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: White House
Budget Director
Mick Mulvaney joins me to
explain the administration's

00:20.253 --> 00:22.122 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
tax reform proposal and
President Trump's
plan to get a spending bill
passed.

00:22.155 --> 00:26.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also ahead, a look at the first
100 days of
the Trump presidency, the
progress and setbacks

00:26.526 --> 00:28.328 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on the domestic front for the
new administration.

00:28.361 --> 00:32.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: a wall keeping people and
wildlife out
-- how a political divide could
endanger animals

00:32.966 --> 00:34.734 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
living along the U.S.-Mexico
border.

00:34.768 --> 00:39.406 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SERGIO AVILA-VILLEGAS,
Arizona-Sonora Desert
Museum: Long-term, this could be
a division

00:39.439 --> 00:45.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of genetical populations, where
a group of
animals from one side cannot
reproduce with

00:45.378 --> 00:51.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
another group of animals,
breaking the connectivity,
creating some genetical
problems.

00:51.317 --> 00:55.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:55.288 --> 00:59.459 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:59.492 --> 01:10.837 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Trump
administration is
out with the broad strokes of
what it says

01:10.870 --> 01:13.173 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
would be the largest tax reform
in U.S. history.

01:13.206 --> 01:17.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The plan's main features,
released today,
include cutting corporate tax
rates to 15

01:17.243 --> 01:18.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
percent from 35 percent.

01:19.012 --> 01:22.715 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It would also consolidate
existing income
tax brackets into just three,
ranging from

01:22.749 --> 01:24.350 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
10 percent to 35 percent.

01:24.384 --> 01:28.655 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it would double the standard
deduction,
while repealing the estate tax.

01:28.688 --> 01:33.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At a White House briefing,
Treasury Secretary
Steven Mnuchin promised the plan
will not

01:34.027 --> 01:35.862 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
make the deficit worse.

01:35.895 --> 01:41.334 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN, U.S. Treasury
Secretary: This
will pay for itself with growth
and with reduced

01:41.367 --> 01:44.070 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
reduction of different
deductions, and closing
loopholes.

01:44.104 --> 01:51.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We will be working very closely,
as I said,
with the House and Senate to
turn this into

01:51.377 --> 01:57.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a bill that can be passed and
the president
can sign, and there's lots and
lots of details

01:57.984 --> 02:00.887 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
going into how that will pay for
itself.

02:00.920 --> 02:07.627 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Republican
leaders said the
plan offers critical guideposts
for a tax

02:07.660 --> 02:13.399 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
overhaul, but Democrats called
it a massive
tax break for the wealthy.

02:13.433 --> 02:21.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On another issue, Secretary
Mnuchin said today
that President Trump -- quote --
"has no intention"

02:21.074 --> 02:23.243 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of making his own tax returns
public.

02:23.276 --> 02:27.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Congress moved closer today to
trying to prevent
a government shutdown on
Saturday.

02:27.814 --> 02:32.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Democrats said one stumbling
block apparently
fell away when the White House
agreed to continue

02:32.919 --> 02:35.155 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
subsidies for millions of poor
people under
Obamacare.

02:35.188 --> 02:38.391 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, conservative House
Republicans
announced that they will back a
newly revised

02:38.424 --> 02:39.592 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
plan to repeal and replace
Obamacare.

02:39.626 --> 02:41.628 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It is not yet clear if moderates
will go along.

02:41.661 --> 02:45.331 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is word that President
Trump has settled
on a course of action against
North Korea.

02:45.365 --> 02:50.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A top national security official
says it begins
with diplomacy, but includes a
range of options.

02:50.103 --> 02:57.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That word came as all 100
senators took a
bus caravan to the White House
for a classified

02:57.076 --> 02:58.511 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
briefing.

02:58.545 --> 03:00.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democrat Chris Coons of Delaware
was among
those who spoke afterwards.

03:00.747 --> 03:02.482 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:02.515 --> 03:05.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRIS COONS (D), Delaware: I was
encouraged
that they chose to brief the
entire Senate.

03:05.285 --> 03:10.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think the -- it was a
sobering briefing,
in which it was clear just how
much thought

03:10.857 --> 03:17.030 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and planning is going into
preparing military
options, if called for, and a
diplomatic strategy

03:17.063 --> 03:20.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that strikes me as clear-eyed
and well -- well-proportioned
to the threat.

03:20.967 --> 03:24.938 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: House members had
their briefing
later at the Capitol.

03:24.971 --> 03:30.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And North Korea issued a new
warning that
it will -- quote -- "go to the
end," apparently

03:30.276 --> 03:34.981 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
meaning a nuclear strike, if
there is an all-out
war with the U.S.

03:35.014 --> 03:39.452 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China today unveiled its first
domestically
built aircraft carrier, the
latest step in

03:39.485 --> 03:41.154 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a major naval expansion.

03:41.187 --> 03:45.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The vessel slowly slipped into
the water in
the port city of Dalian to much
fanfare.

03:45.725 --> 03:50.063 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It is expected to become
operational by 2020,
after undergoing sea trials.

03:50.096 --> 03:54.901 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump today decried a
new legal
blow to his immigration policy.

03:54.934 --> 04:01.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On Tuesday, a federal district
judge in San
Francisco blocked his order to
withhold funding

04:01.074 --> 04:07.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from so-called sanctuary cities,
which seek
to protect many of those who are
undocumented.

04:07.880 --> 04:13.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president tweeted that the
decision was
-- quote -- "ridiculous" and he
vowed to appeal.

04:13.486 --> 04:19.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He lumped that in with criticism
of the 9th
Judicial Circuit, where
appellate courts also

04:19.359 --> 04:20.893 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
blocked his travel ban.

04:20.927 --> 04:22.629 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Later, he echoed that complaint:

04:22.662 --> 04:25.999 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
I'm never surprised by the 9th
Circuit.

04:26.032 --> 04:27.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

04:27.333 --> 04:29.202 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: As I said, we will
see them
in the Supreme Court.

04:29.235 --> 04:35.241 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Mr. Trump also
told The Washington
Examiner newspaper that he has
considered

04:35.275 --> 04:37.977 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
proposals to split up the 9th
Circuit.

04:38.011 --> 04:43.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, the Department of
Homeland Security
formally opened a new office to
help victims

04:43.483 --> 04:45.451 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of crimes by undocumented
immigrants.

04:45.485 --> 04:51.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Secretary John Kelly said that
it will help
shine a light on victims as part
of the president's

04:51.224 --> 04:52.992 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
push on illegal immigration.

04:53.026 --> 04:55.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Multiple studies show that
native-born Americans
are more likely to commit crimes
than are

04:55.862 --> 04:57.630 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
immigrants.

04:57.664 --> 04:59.932 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Trump administration is
going to review
so-called national monument
designations for

04:59.966 --> 05:01.501 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
millions of acres of federal
land.

05:01.534 --> 05:04.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They go back to President
Clinton's time in
office.

05:04.170 --> 05:07.640 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mr. Trump ordered the review at
the U.S. Interior
Department today.

05:07.674 --> 05:11.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is aimed at what he called a
-- quote -- "massive
federal land grab" that bars
drilling, mining

05:11.944 --> 05:13.346 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and other uses.

05:13.379 --> 05:16.082 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Environmental and Native
American tribal groups
denounced the action.

05:16.115 --> 05:17.884 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Wall Street gave a little
ground today.

05:17.917 --> 05:21.621 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
lost 21 points
to close at 20975.

05:21.654 --> 05:27.860 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell a quarter of a
point, and
the S&amp;P 500 slipped one point.

05:27.894 --> 05:34.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
I sit down
with White House Budget Director
Mick Mulvaney

05:34.334 --> 05:38.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to talk about the president's
budget and tax
priorities; approaching
President Trump's

05:38.237 --> 05:44.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
first 100 days in office, a look
at what he
has accomplished here at home;
and much more.

05:44.377 --> 05:52.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On this day when the White House
is unveiling
the outline of a tax system
overhaul, and

05:52.185 --> 05:56.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
negotiating down to the wire
over a federal
spending plan to fund the
government through

05:56.789 --> 06:01.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
September, I sat down with Mick
Mulvaney,
the head of the Office of
Management and Budget.

06:01.527 --> 06:07.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I spoke with him at his office
this afternoon,
before there were reports of a
deal on health

06:07.500 --> 06:08.868 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
care subsidies.

06:08.901 --> 06:15.375 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Director Mick Mulvaney, thank
you very much
for talking with us.

06:15.408 --> 06:22.682 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY, White House
Budget Director:
Judy, thank you for having me.

06:22.715 --> 06:29.956 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I do want to
start by asking
you about taxes.

06:29.989 --> 06:34.727 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's the big announcement
coming from the
administration today.

06:34.761 --> 06:36.696 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MICK MULVANEY: Sure.

06:36.729 --> 06:39.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The proposal,
among other things,
calls for increases in the
standard deductions,

06:39.132 --> 06:40.099 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
individuals and families.

06:40.133 --> 06:41.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MICK MULVANEY: Yes.

06:41.300 --> 06:42.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Big cuts in
corporate business
taxes.

06:42.735 --> 06:47.540 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What is the administration
trying to accomplish
with this proposal?

06:47.573 --> 06:51.310 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY: Getting economic
growth back
where it's supposed to be.

06:51.344 --> 06:54.247 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think what we have forgotten
for the last
decade is that America used to
be a fast-growing

06:54.280 --> 06:56.082 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
economy.

06:56.115 --> 07:00.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you look over the course of
our 200-plus
years, we're supposed to grow at
about 3 percent,

07:00.119 --> 07:06.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on average, and that's where we
have been
since World War II, at the very
least, even

07:06.125 --> 07:07.994 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
further back than that.

07:08.027 --> 07:12.331 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, for the last decade, we
have been growing
at less than 2 percent.

07:12.365 --> 07:17.370 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That doesn't sound like much,
but if you think
about it in terms of the power
of compound

07:17.403 --> 07:22.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
interest, when you take an
economy our size
that only grows 2 percent a year
for a decade,

07:22.475 --> 07:26.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
instead of 3 percent a year, the
difference
between those things are
tremendous.

07:26.212 --> 07:29.782 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Folks who are 30 years old have
never had
a job during a time when the
economy was growing

07:29.816 --> 07:30.783 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
at 3 percent.

07:30.817 --> 07:32.318 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And it's entirely different.

07:32.351 --> 07:36.022 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I was a young person, if
you got fired,
you could find another job.

07:36.055 --> 07:39.292 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you wanted to quit, you could
go start
your own company.

07:39.325 --> 07:41.461 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We haven't had that for 10 years
now.

07:41.494 --> 07:43.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we're trying to get back to
that.

07:43.329 --> 07:48.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that is what is driving not
only everything
we do at the White House, but
specifically

07:48.167 --> 07:49.836 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this tax plan.

07:49.869 --> 07:57.043 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A number of the
analysts who
have looked at say, when you put
together

07:57.076 --> 08:02.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the proposed business tax cuts,
some of the
individual cuts, and when you
look at the

08:02.715 --> 08:11.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
proposal to do away with some of
the taxes
that are now in the Affordable
Care Act, in

08:11.224 --> 08:15.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
essence, it's the top 1 percent
of Americans,
1 percent of American,
high-income level,

08:15.461 --> 08:19.599 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who are going to benefit the
most from this.

08:19.632 --> 08:21.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How do you answer that?

08:21.167 --> 08:25.338 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY: I'm not sure how
could they
could come to that conclusion.

08:25.371 --> 08:30.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would be curious to know what
assumptions
they're making regarding the
value of deductions.

08:30.610 --> 08:34.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For example, we get rid of all
the deductions
on the personal side, except, I
think, let's

08:34.480 --> 08:36.983 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
see, charity and some of the
home interest
deduction.

08:37.016 --> 08:42.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I'm not sure how you could
make that conclusion,
unless you're making some wild
assumptions

08:42.121 --> 08:44.123 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about the nature of those
deductions.

08:44.156 --> 08:47.460 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Where do you see
the benefits
falling, what income?

08:47.493 --> 08:49.095 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY: Middle class.

08:49.128 --> 08:52.365 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Middle class and business, writ
large, both
large business and small
business.

08:52.398 --> 08:58.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, it should be one of the
largest reductions
on small business, what we call
S Corporations,

08:58.938 --> 09:00.806 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in the history of S
Corporations.

09:00.840 --> 09:03.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we're trying to drive the
economic benefit
here to the taxpayers in the
middle, the folks

09:03.776 --> 09:08.648 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who are in the middle class, who
are paying
the taxes, and the places where
they work.

09:08.681 --> 09:12.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We know the tax
cuts for these
so-called pass-through
businesses, owner-owned

09:12.184 --> 09:14.120 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
businesses, are going to be
among the beneficiaries.

09:14.153 --> 09:17.456 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We know President Trump, it's
the kind of
business he has.

09:17.490 --> 09:19.592 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How much does he stand to
benefit?

09:19.625 --> 09:24.764 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I ask people of because
people are saying,
we don't know what his tax
income situation

09:24.797 --> 09:25.765 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
is.

09:25.798 --> 09:27.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He has said he's not going to
release that.

09:27.867 --> 09:30.803 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How does the public know that he
doesn't stand
to benefit significantly?

09:30.836 --> 09:33.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY: Well, I actually
don't care
about whether or not someone
else benefits.

09:33.839 --> 09:35.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I care about whether I benefit,
I being just
anybody.

09:35.975 --> 09:37.376 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

09:37.410 --> 09:39.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As long as I'm better off, why
should I care
if somebody is as well?

09:39.545 --> 09:44.150 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What I look at through is the
lens of the
business I used to run.

09:44.183 --> 09:45.151 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I owned a restaurant.

09:45.184 --> 09:46.852 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was a fast, fresh Mexican
restaurant.

